You are a real-time systems architect specializing in WebSocket APIs.

Given this requirement:
- ID: WA-PROF-003
- Title: Info/Status Text
- Description: Das System MUSS einen kurzen Info-Text im Profil unterstuetzen

Derive WebSocket channels and events needed for real-time features.

Return JSON format:
{
    "channels": [
        {
            "name": "chat/messages",
            "description": "Real-time chat message delivery",
            "subscribe": {
                "name": "ChatMessageReceived",
                "description": "Incoming message from another user",
                "fields": {
                    "message_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Unique message ID"},
                    "sender_id": {"type": "string", "description": "Sender user ID"},
                    "content": {"type": "string", "description": "Message content"},
                    "timestamp": {"type": "string", "format": "date-time"}
                }
            },
            "publish": {
                "name": "SendChatMessage",
                "description": "Send a new message",
                "fields": {
                    "conversation_id": {"type": "string"},
                    "content": {"type": "string"},
                    "type": {"type": "string", "enum": ["text", "image", "file"]}
                }
            },
            "parameters": {
                "conversation_id": "string"
            }
        }
    ]
}

Guidelines:
- Use hierarchical channel names (e.g., "chat/messages", "user/presence", "call/signal")
- subscribe = events FROM server TO client (receiving)
- publish = events FROM client TO server (sending)
- Include all necessary fields with types
- Consider acknowledgment events where needed
- Only include channels directly related to the requirement

Return ONLY valid JSON.

{
  "channels": [
    {
      "name": "profile/status",
      "description": "Real-time updates for user profile info/status text",
      "subscribe": {
        "name": "ProfileStatusUpdated",
        "description": "Server notifies clients that a user's status text has changed",
        "fields": {
          "user_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "User whose status text changed"
          },
          "status_text": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Short info/status text"
          },
          "updated_at": {
            "type": "string",
            "format": "date-time",
            "description": "Timestamp of the update"
          }
        }
      },
      "publish": {
        "name": "UpdateProfileStatus",
        "description": "Client updates their own status text",
        "fields": {
          "status_text": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "New short info/status text"
          }
        }
      },
      "parameters": {
        "user_id": "string"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "profile/status/ack",
      "description": "Acknowledgment channel for profile status updates",
      "subscribe": {
        "name": "ProfileStatusUpdateAck",
        "description": "Server acknowledges status text update",
        "fields": {
          "request_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Client-generated request ID"
          },
          "status": {
            "type": "string",
            "enum": [
              "accepted",
              "rejected"
            ]
          },
          "error": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Error message if rejected"
          }
        }
      },
      "publish": {
        "name": "ProfileStatusUpdateRequest",
        "description": "Client sends update request with correlation ID",
        "fields": {
          "request_id": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Client-generated request ID"
          },
          "status_text": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "New short info/status text"
          }
        }
      },
      "parameters": {
        "user_id": "string"
      }
    }
  ]
}

